args: Um, what are you doing, Mym?
I feel like you're trying to prevent me\nfrom getting past you.
I hear you're looking for something\nyou can do to help out around here.
Th-that's right. I'll happily do anything\nI can to be of service to you all.
Wh-where are you taking me?\nHey! Stop pulling me!
All right, that's the door locked.\nNo one saw us come here, right?
I don't think so. Do you have something\nsecret that you need to tell me?
Of course it's a secret! You don't normally\nlet everyone know when you're trying to\nbetter yourself, do you?
Oh! Well, of course I'm happy to try,\nbut if I may ask, what brought this on?
My darling says your dancing is pretty.
Which means that if I can do it,\nhe'll love me all the more!
＂I want to see you do it every day\nfor me and me alone!＂
THAT'S how he's going to react. *siiigh*
Ummm... So basically, you want to learn\nfor {player_name}'s sake?
Then I'll be happy to help.
I'm actually kind of jealous of the way\nyou're able to declare your love\nwithout hesitation like that.
I can't even come out and say\nI love my dancing.
In fact, I don't even know if I should say\nI LIKE my dancing anymore.
Oh, that's what you meant. I thought for a\nsecond I'd gained another rival.
Never mind. Go back to the part where\nyou were carping about your dancing.
Oh, I didn't really mean it like that.
I just can't help but feel that if I hadn't\nstarted dancing, it would have prevented\nall sorts of terrible things.
Thanatos would never have shown\nany interest in me, my home would\nnever have been destroyed...
Without dancing, you'd likely be living\na peaceful, happy life somewhere.
But your dancing has ALSO made\na lot of people happy, right?
I'm sorry for how things have turned out,\nbut no one can reverse time.
And looking gloomy isn't going to\nbring your village back.
Do you really think your family and friends\nwould want you being sad all the time?
Then you should hold your head high\nand tell the world you love dancing.
That's the best way to remember\neveryone you care about.
Thank you, Mym. I feel like a weight\nhas been lifted off my shoulders.
From now on, I'm going to proudly tell\neveryone that I love to dance.
Now THAT'S the kind of moxie\nI want to see from my instructor!
I'm glad. Shall we begin, then?
Absolutely! ...So what do I do?\nStrut about? Shake my booty?
Er, let's start with the basic posture.\nPlease stand with your legs together.
Keep your thighs together,\nand don't arc your back.
Er, do you mind if I touch you?\nThat will make this easier.
Well, your legs need to be like this...\nAnd your back should be like this...\nOh, wait. Don't raise your shoulders.
With practice, it will feel natural and\ngive you a graceful posture.
Next, I want you to try walking while\nmaintaining this same pose.
Wait! Just move your legs—\nnot the rest of you.
That's it! Your form is perfect.
Hrm... This is harder than I had\nfirst anticipated.
Next, I need you to keep that posture\nwhile performing some basic steps.
It will be more complicated than walking,\nbut you must maintain that form.
Just follow what I do. Ready?\nOne, two, three! One, two, three!
Ugh. This is MUCH harder than I\nthought it was going to be.
It's certainly not easy—but don't worry.\nI'll stay with you until you can do it.
Ack! Wait, hold it! Time out!\nI just heard something snap!
